entities.description:
Changes a user's password for a specified network server or domain. Note: This function does not control how the oldpassword and newpassword parameters are secured when sent over the network to a remote server. Any encryption of these parameters is handled by the Remote Procedure Call (RPC) mechanism, which is supported by the network redirector providing the transport. Encryption is also controlled by the security mechanisms supported by the local computer and by the remote network server or domain specified in the domainname parameter.

